values:
I am so excited for Harry and the Potters tonight! I'm also slighlty excited for Math the Band...but I can't seem to have enough Enthusiasm (heh) for Uncle Monster Face.&nbsp;

I think part of what I'm excited about is that they're&nbsp;playing in an actual theatre...rather than the&nbsp;basement of the Denver Public Library. Now, don't get me wrong, I've seen them there twice and loved every second of it, but at least this time they'll be on an&nbsp;ACTUAL stage and when really mean tall people stand in front of me it shouldn't matter too much. I hope. &nbsp;bascially, I'm super psyched. one could even say that I have Unlimited Enthusiasm....


or, you know. not.

we haven't&nbsp;had internet/cable/regular tv for about a week and a half. It's nice to&nbsp;finally be able to just lounge and watch bad tv rather than watching episode after episode of gilmore girls. Don't get me wrong, I LOVE that show, but...yikes.&nbsp;
so, we've moved. Phil and I are on our own, just the two of us, with the&nbsp;amazing Patronus. (and the cat.) It has been fantastic. I was really concerned, somewhere, in the back of my mind, so not&nbsp;REALLY that things would turn suddenly bad, or that living with the variety of people I have lived with has fulfilled my&nbsp;need to&nbsp;have drama in my life, but now living with just Phil, would I need something&nbsp;to complain about? Not yet, and I don't realistcally forseeing it happen. I don''t know how Phil and I ended up together, but we did and things continue to be great, every day. My heart still flip fliops when I hear his key in the door, and soon he switches to the day shift which means we will&nbsp;have a real,&nbsp;grown-up life together, rather than seeing&nbsp;each other for 20 minutes a day (except on weds and thurs. and sat and sun. then it's a couple hours.) i'm really excited to be able to come &nbsp;home to him, to have dinner with him, and to have date nights again.&nbsp;
and in other news, Patronus is almost a Certified Canine Good Citizen, as he graduates from his advanced dog class in a couple weeks. I am so excited, because once he gets certified he can come to work with me and be a therapy dog, with his magical healing powers and great big ears ready for listening.
